==English==
===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1393|1393]], from [[Latin]] ''simile'', neuter of ''[[similis]]'' ''"[[like]], [[similar]]"''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-simile.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{cattag|linguistics}} a [[figure of speech]] in which one thing is compared to another, generally using ''like'' or ''as''.
#:*''"A woman without a man is like a fish without a bicycle"'' &mdash; [[w:Irina Dunn|Irina Dunn]], [[w:1970|1970]]
#:''A '''simile''' is like a metaphor.'' <!-- I almost deleted this but thought Wiktionary can afford a little fun. -->

